WASD  are  used  to  go  forward,  left,
backward, or  right, respectively. These
controls TOGGLE, so you press the button
again  to  stop  (or another  button  to
start moving a different direction.)

Keys Q  and E are  used to turn  left or
right,  respectively. These  controls do
NOT toggle.

To  shoot, press  SPACE.  You can  shoot
while  pressing another  key by  holding
SHIFT  or switching  on  CAPS LOCK.  You
will  reload  independently of  pressing
any key.

To pause the current level, press P.

To quit the level, press X.
